data.chText: 冗长的；啰唆的；单调乏味的；令人厌烦的
data.enText: lasting or taking too long and not interesting

data.chText: 那次旅行不久就变得乏味起来。
我们不得不听他唠叨他那次行动繁琐的细节。
data.enText: We had to listen to the tedious details of his operation.

data.chText: 以上各词均形容课题、活动、人或地方等没意思、乏味。
data.enText: These words all describe a subject, activity, person or place that is not interesting or exciting.

data.chText: 指没有趣味的、令人厌倦或厌烦的：
data.enText: not interesting; making you feel tired and impatient

data.chText: 他就是这么一个惹人烦的人！
她觉得自己的工作很无聊。
data.enText: She found her job very boring.

data.chText: 小城镇的生活可能会非常没意思。
data.enText: Life in a small town could be deadly dull.

data.chText: 指冗长的、单调乏味的、令人厌烦的：
data.enText: lasting or taking too long and not interesting, so that you feel bored and impatient

data.chText: 那次旅行不久就变得乏味起来。

data.enText: not attracting your interest or attention

data.chText: 食物单调得很，一点也不吸引人。
data.enText: The food was dull and uninteresting.

data.chText: 指干巴巴的、枯燥无味的：
data.enText: boring because it lacks human interest

data.chText: 政府报告读起来往往枯燥无味。
data.enText: Government reports tend to make dry reading.

tr: using or containing too many words
example: newspapers of the day printed long wordy editorials
proceedings were delayed by wordy disputes

tr: so lacking in interest as to cause mental weariness
example: a boring evening with uninteresting people
the deadening effect of some routine tasks
a ho-hum speaker who couldn't capture their attention
what an irksome task the writing of long letters is"- Edmund Burk
the tiresome chirping of a cricket"- Mark Twai
other people's dreams are dreadfully wearisome

value.def: If you describe something such as a job, task, or situation as tedious, you mean it is boring and rather frustrating.

example.ex: Such lists are long and tedious to read.
example.tran: 这种表单读起来冗长乏味。
枯燥乏味的逐行编程工作

value.tran: 枯燥的;乏味的;令人生厌的

example.ex: ...the most tediously boring aspects of international relations.
example.tran: 国际关系中最枯燥乏味的方面
